comments: Embiid (PHI) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Korkmaz (PHI) makes incidental contact with Jackson's (LAC) right arm after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Jackson (LAC) overtly kicks his right leg out during the follow-through of his jump shot attempt, and marginal contact with Korkmaz (PHI) occurs.
Batum (LAC) makes contact with the ball for the tap-out rebound prior to making incidental contact with Maxey's (PHI) left hand.
Embiid (PHI) and Coffey (LAC) engage and disengage with one another during the screen.
Batum (LAC) makes contact with the ball and he legally dislodges it from Embiid (PHI).

Embiid (PHI) swipes down and his arm brushes Zubac's (LAC) head following the release. The incidental contact does not affect Zubac's shot attempt near the rim. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.

Jackson (LAC) applies a left arm across Harris' (PHI) front and restricts his FOM into the paint area. Replay review of the defensive foul called on Jackson (LAC) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.
Zubac (LAC) faces up and holds Embiid's (PHI) arm which affects his FOM during the rebound.

Embiid (PHI) raises both arms and his left elbow makes incidental contact to Batum's (LAC) head/face during an attempt to receive the pass in the post. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed incidental when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Korkmaz (PHI) delivers contact to Jackson's (LAC) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Embiid (PHI) reaches in and makes contact with Zubac's (LAC) arm that affects his FOM.
Zubac (LAC) jumps from point A to point B and he delivers contact to Embiid's (PHI) body that affects his driving shot attempt. Zubac's hand comes down and makes contact to Embid's arm as well.
Embiid (PHI) commits a take foul on Jackson (LAC).
Niang (PHI) commits the take foul on Morris Sr. (LAC).
Harris (PHI) and Jackson (LAC) mutually engage in marginal arm to arm contact as both players attempt to get to the rebound.

Prior to the called out of bounds, both players go to the floor as they pursue the loose ball. After Morris Sr. gathers the ball, Niang turns and his elbow makes incidental contact to Morris Sr.'s head. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed incidental when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Jackson (LAC) maintains a legal guarding position during Maxey's (PHI) drive.
